Usage:
        This is an extension to the CSiBE environment for measuring execution
        time. To measure execution time simply decompress the  files into the
        CSiBE base directory  and  create  a  new configuration (for this see
        `CSiBE-README').  After this `cd'  to the newly created configuration
        directory   and   type  `make result-runtime.csv'.  If  the parameter
        `runtime' is given to the switch `-R' (either alone or in addition to
        `size'  and/or  `time')   when  the  new  configuration  is  created,
        `make result' will automatically create the `result-runtime.csv' file
        as well.
        Note, that the linking of some programs requires additional libraries
        (e.g. libz).  Without these libraries, no runtime can be measured for
        those programs.

